<TITLE> Bloomsbury profits boosted by Harry Potter books </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 London, April 1 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Publisher Bloomsbury Publishing Plc posted a 243 percent rise in full year profit on Tuesday, boosted by strong sales of Harry Potter books, and said it has a strong pipeline of new titles for the year ahead. Bloomsbury, which also publishes The Kite Runner, said pretax profit was 17.86 million pounds ($35.49 million), within the range of analyst forecasts according to a Reuters Estimates Poll, for 2007. Revenue doubled to 150.21 million. "We are now well positioned for the post Harry Potter era," Chief Executive Nigel Newton said in the results statement.
